examples.en: They preferred to settle the matter one-on-one.
They much preferred country life to life in the city.
Which one is the preferred alternative?
Her preferred form of headgear is a big, floppy hat.
She preferred the black nylon number.
I think I preferred the television version.
The series B preferred stock will not accrue dividends.
Nelson preferred to lead the attack himself from the front.
What is the preferred pronunciation of her name?
He preferred a single materiality to a slew of hypotheticals.
Senior officials would have preferred a more pliable government.
A company pays dividends on both its common and preferred shares.
Coffins are said to be the preferred sleeping places of vampires.
His work was preferred from the cellar of the publishers to the author's garret.
